FBIS4-9972 "drlat066_m_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 Brazil New Environment Minister To Continue Ricupero's Work New Environment Minister To Continue Ricupero's Work PY0604014294 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 2200 GMT 5 Apr 94 PY0604014294 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network Portuguese BFN [Report by Claudia Moreira from Brasilia] [Text] Environment Minister Henrique Brandao Cavalcanti was installed this morning. He is a civil engineer who was the coordinator for Amazon affairs. Brandao Cavalcanti said the policy of his ministry will continue unchanged. [Begin Brandao Cavalcanti recording] The first step is to continue Minister Ricupero's work. In the case of the Amazon region, I will continue the work of the National Amazon Region Council, which has a schedule already established for the 10 work-groups that cover the various areas. We will strictly comply with this schedule. As to the environment, there are many aspects. Minister Ricupero has expressed concern for the multiple aspects of the issue: the forests and the national parks which call for the establishment of some priorities. To meet this objective, I will consult experts who are already working in the ministry and who are responsible for them. [end recording] Henrique Brandao Cavalcanti will stimulate the decentralization process and make action in the environmental area more effective. He believes the Environment Ministry will develop more as a result of Minister Ricupero's installation as finance minister.
